On World Intellectual Property Day, President Donald Trump issued a proclamation highlighting the importance of innovation in the economy. He emphasized the need to protect intellectual property and related technologies to foster new industries and innovations. Trump mentioned the Orrin G. Hatch–Bob Goodlatte Music Modernization Act, which improves copyright laws to ensure fair compensation for musicians. He also highlighted the United States–Mexico–Canada Agreement (USMCA), which includes strong intellectual property standards. Trump stated that the protection of intellectual property is crucial for economic growth, job creation, and national security. The theme of this year's World Intellectual Property Day is intellectual property in sports, recognizing its role in advancing athletes' abilities and enhancing the enjoyment of sports for fans. Trump encouraged Americans to observe the day with events and educational programs celebrating the benefits of intellectual property.